The paper discusses the challenges faced by UX practitioners in incorporating machine learning into end user facing systems. This suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the need to consider the long tail of machine learning, which could relate to the categories of cybernetics (cs.CY), information retrieval (cs.IR), and machine learning (cs.LG).
